<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-03T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-03T14:00:00-05:00" n="39" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d39">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1912: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Bolivia (<persName type="to">Feely</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-03T15:00:00-04:00">August
                                        3, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>23. Your 46, August 1, 5 p.m. Suggestion for immediate armistice was
                                made in telegram sent by the Neutrals to Minister of Foreign Affairs
                                of Bolivia yesterday.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>